    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instruments composed of lead, often encased in wood or another support. Distinct from "graphite pencils," which in the 19th century were misleadingly called lead pencils.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
